@startuml oc-ms-lifecycle-state
' OC MS runtime Optimisation lifecycle state model
' Focus: runtime execution, cancellation, cancellation failure, and retrial creation context.

hide empty description
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
  FontColor Black
}

title OC MS - Runtime Optimisation lifecycle state model

[*] --> ACKNOWLEDGED : POST /optimisation\ncreationContext.reason = NEW\nOC persists resource and outbox

FAILED --> ACKNOWLEDGED : POST /optimisation/{id}/retrial\ncreates new Optimisation\ncreationContext.reason = RETRIAL\nrelationshipType = retrialOf

ACKNOWLEDGED --> QUEUED : outbox publish succeeds
QUEUED --> PROCESSING : worker-start signal accepted by OC MS

PROCESSING --> COMPLETED : OptimisationCompletedEvent.status = COMPLETED
PROCESSING --> INFEASIBLE : OptimisationCompletedEvent.status = INFEASIBLE
PROCESSING --> FAILED : OptimisationCompletedEvent.status = FAILED

ACKNOWLEDGED --> CANCELLING : POST cancellation accepted\nstate + cancel outbox committed
QUEUED --> CANCELLING : POST cancellation accepted\nstate + cancel outbox committed
PROCESSING --> CANCELLING : POST cancellation accepted\nstate + cancel outbox committed

CANCELLING --> CANCELLED : OptimisationCompletedEvent.status = CANCELLED
CANCELLING --> CANCELLATIONFAILED : OptimisationCompletedEvent.status = CANCELLATIONFAILED

CANCELLATIONFAILED --> COMPLETED : later terminal outcome\nstatus = COMPLETED
CANCELLATIONFAILED --> INFEASIBLE : later terminal outcome\nstatus = INFEASIBLE
CANCELLATIONFAILED --> FAILED : later terminal outcome\nstatus = FAILED

COMPLETED --> [*]
INFEASIBLE --> [*]
FAILED --> [*] : terminal unless retrial creates a new Optimisation
CANCELLED --> [*]

ACKNOWLEDGED : Accepted and persisted
ACKNOWLEDGED : Outbox event written

QUEUED : Requested event published
QUEUED : Waiting for worker processing

PROCESSING : Worker has started or is preparing execution

COMPLETED : Terminal success outcome
INFEASIBLE : Terminal optimisation outcome
FAILED : Terminal technical or runtime failure

CANCELLING : Cancellation accepted
CANCELLING : Cancel instruction is durable
CANCELLING : Final cancellation not confirmed yet

CANCELLED : Terminal cancellation outcome
CANCELLATIONFAILED : Non-terminal cancellation-command outcome
CANCELLATIONFAILED : Optimisation may still continue
CANCELLATIONFAILED : self link only in baseline

note right of CANCELLATIONFAILED
CANCELLATIONFAILED must not suppress or block
later valid terminal outcomes.
It is not retriable in the baseline.
If it later reaches FAILED, retrial may then be requested from FAILED.
end note

note bottom of FAILED
Retrial is an action, not a lifecycle state.
A successful retrial creates a new Optimisation with:
creationContext.reason = RETRIAL
optimisationRelationship.relationshipType = retrialOf
The original Optimisation remains FAILED.
end note

note bottom
The current Kafka event baseline remains limited to:
OptimisationRequestedEvent
OptimisationCompletedEvent
No separate progress, retrial, or cancellation-failed event type is introduced.
end note

@enduml
